race.comment: Lots of these will appreciate getting back to country grade. MRS PENNY CRACKER (5) has been closing in on a win, the latest running on hard to place at the provincials. Will stalk the pace off a low draw and looks hard to hold out again. LADY VANHUSEN (4) was good fresh when winding up late at the provincials then not disgraced at Morphettville last time when got too far back. Much better placed here. PRINCE LUCIFER (7) returned from a long break at the provincials and finished fourth in a solid return. Blinkers added and fitter again. Has upside. OLDPOP (6) is better than last start and can back in trip.
